What does this word/name mean? Words’ meaning, dictionary definition, explanation, information.
Information & Source
Oonagh
MEANING OF THE IRISH NAME OONAGH. LISTEN AND LEARN HOW TO PRONOUNCE OONAGH SO YOU CAN GET THE CORRECT PRONUNCIATION FOR THIS IRISH GIRL NAME.
MEANING: From the Irish word uan “a lamb” or may come from the Latin unameaning “one,” hence it is sometimes translated as “Unity.” In legend Oonagh was “Queen of the Fairies” who had long golden hair which reached to the ground and she was also the wife of Fionn Mac Cool (read the legend).
Source: https://babynamesofireland.com/oonagh
GENDER: Girl | Female

IRISH NAME: Oonagh Oona Una
PRONUNCIATION: ou + na”

ENGLISH:
